Reasoning: The paper deals with fundamental barriers in the theory of computations and establishes a new extended theory of complexity. It also provides algorithms to compute solutions to basic problems in computations and establishes absolute barriers for what can be achieved computationally. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper deals with numerical algorithms and error control, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also deals with solving linear equations and Schrodinger operators, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of control systems and optimization (cs.SY) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
